Notice of Case Status Change - Defendant Terminated 05/05/15
  Wis. Dept. of Corrections notice of case status change received.  Outstanding financial obligations have been satisfied.
with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Vinson B Teuteberg in court with attorney Amber K Rumpf.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State filed an Amended Information.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

Court orders the following:
- 6 months Huber with standard release conditions. STAYED
- 1 year Probation. 
- Court costs of $243.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge waived
- Buy money of $400.00 to be paid to the Metro Drug Unit as a Condition of Probation.
- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Continue with AODA treatment.  
CONDITION TIME: 30 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - STAYED for use by Agent.
Defendant waives his/her right to a Preliminary Hearing.

Defendant Vinson B Teuteberg in court with attorney Amber Kay Rumpf.  Susan L. Opper appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant waives his/her right to a Preliminary Hearing, bound over. Information filed, reading waived.   NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED. 
  Hearing scheduled for May 5, 2014 at 09:00 am.
